  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    PasswordCheckerInterface
    PasswordCheckerInterface
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    GuiDriver
    GuiDriver class is the Gui driver This is where the Gui stage is set up and creates a new Gui Main
    GuiMain
    GuiMain Prompts user to enter a password and re-type the password It is where the password, file, exit buttons, textfields and labels are created, exceptions are thrown, and PasswordChecker class is called
    PasswordChecker
    PasswordChecker This class is used to check if the password is valid If it is invalid the proper exception will be thrown in the conditional statements
    PasswordCheckerTest
    Test the methods of PasswordChecker
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    InvalidSequenceException
    InvalidSequenceException checks the string for a sequence of more than two characters Passes error message to the super class exception
    LengthException
    LengthException checks the string to see if the length is less than 8 Passes error message to the super class exception
    NoDigitException
    NoDigitException checks the string to see if there is no digit Passes error message to the super class exception
    NoLowerAlphaException
    NoLowerAlphaException checks the string to see if there is no lowercase Passes error message to the super class exception
    NoUpperAlphaException
    NoUpperAlphaException checks the string to see if there is no uppercase Passes error message to the super class exception
    UnmatchedException
    UnmatchedException checks the string to see if it matches the re-type password Passes error message to the super class exception
